o-style\"><div id=\"pgc-3157-4-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\"><div id=\"panel-3157-4-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_black-studio-tinymce widget_black_studio_tinymce panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"6\"><div class=\"textwidget\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3411\" src=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-27-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-27-200x300.jpg 200w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-27-100x150.jpg 100w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-27-150x225.jpg 150w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-27.jpg 213w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-3423\" src=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-12-1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-12-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-12-1-100x67.jpg 100w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-12-1-150x100.jpg 150w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-12-1-200x133.jpg 200w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-12-1-272x182.jpg 272w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-12-1.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 221px) 100vw, 221px\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-3420\" src=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-26-1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-26-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-26-1-100x67.jpg 100w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-26-1-150x100.jpg 150w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-26-1-200x133.jpg 200w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-26-1-272x182.jpg 272w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-26-1.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 212px) 100vw, 212px\"> &nbsp; &nbsp; <img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-3409\" src=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-24-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-24-300x200.jpg 300w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-24-100x67.jpg 100w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-24-150x100.jpg 150w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-24-200x133.jpg 200w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-24-272x182.jpg 272w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-24.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 212px) 100vw, 212px\">&nbsp; &nbsp; <img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3419\" src=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-2-1-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-2-1-200x300.jpg 200w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-2-1-100x150.jpg 100w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-2-1-150x225.jpg 150w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-2-1.jpg 213w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-3414 alignleft\" src=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-16-1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-16-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-16-1-100x67.jpg 100w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-16-1-150x100.jpg 150w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-16-1-200x133.jpg 200w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-16-1-272x182.jpg 272w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/stairs-16-1.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\">&nbsp; &nbsp; <img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-3310 alignleft\" src=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/IMG_9147-1-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/IMG_9147-1-300x225.jpg 300w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/IMG_9147-1-100x75.jpg 100w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/IMG_9147-1-150x113.jpg 150w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/IMG_9147-1-200x150.jpg 200w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/IMG_9147-1.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></p>\n</div></div></div></div><div id=\"pg-3157-5\" class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\"><div id=\"pgc-3157-5-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\"><div id=\"panel-3157-5-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_black-studio-tinymce widget_black_studio_tinymce panel-first-child\" data-index=\"7\"><div class=\"textwidget\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-3868 aligncenter\" src=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/coaster-proof-281x300.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/coaster-proof-281x300.png 281w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/coaster-proof-100x107.png 100w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/coaster-proof-150x160.png 150w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/coaster-proof-200x214.png 200w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/coaster-proof-300x321.png 300w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/coaster-proof-450x481.png 450w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/coaster-proof-280x299.png 280w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/coaster-proof.png 567w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 167px) 100vw, 167px\"> The importance of the Camas Plants to our local History.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The Kalapoya natives came to Beaverton, OR area to harvest camas plants, which were a vital food source for them. They practice sustainable harvesting techniques, ensuring the plants thrived for future generations, and camas played a significant role in their cultural practices and seasonal ceremonies.</li>\n<li><strong>Kalapoya Natives and the Beaverton Area</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Historical Presence</strong></li>\n<li>The Kalapoya people originally occupied a vast area in the Willamette Valley. Including regions that encompass modern-day Beaverton, OR. They have lived in this area for over 14,000 years, developing a deep connection to the land and its resources.</li>\n<li><strong>Importance of Camas Plants</strong></li>\n<li>Camas plants were a vital food source for the Kalapoya. The bulbs of the camas plant were harvested and prepared as a stable in their diet. This plant not only provided nourishment but also played a significant role in their cultural practices.</li>\n<li><strong>Harvesting Practices</strong></li>\n<li>The Kalapoya practiced sustainable harvesting methods for camas, ensuring that the plants could thrive for future generations. They used traditional techniques, such as baking the bulbs in underground ovens, to make them edible. This careful stewardship of the land and its resources reflects their deep understanding of the ecosystem.</li>\n<li><strong>Cultural Significance</strong></li>\n<li>Camas are considered a cultural keystone species, integral to the identity and traditions of the Kalapoya. The plant’s growth stages were often used as seasonal markers in their calendars, linking their agricultural practices to the rhythms of nature.&nbsp; The Kalapoya’s presence in the Beaverton area was driven by the availability of the camas and other resources, which were essential for their survival and cultural practice.</li>\n<li>The Kalapoya natives came to Beaverton, OR area to harvest camas plants, which were a vital food source for them. They practice sustainable harvesting techniques, ensuring the plants thrived for future generations, and camas played a significant role in their cultural practices and seasonal ceremonies.</li>\n<li><strong>Kalapoya Natives and the Beaverton Area</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Historical Presence</strong></li>\n<li>The Kalapoya people originally occupied a vast area in the Willamette Valley. Including regions that encompass modern-day Beaverton, OR. They have lived in this area for over 14,000 years, developing a deep connection to the land and its resources.</li>\n<li><strong>Importance of Camas Plants</strong></li>\n<li>Camas plants were a vital food source for the Kalapoya. The bulbs of the camas plant were harvested and prepared as a stable in their diet. This plant not only provided nourishment but also played a significant role in their cultural practices.</li>\n<li><strong>Harvesting Practices</strong></li>\n<li>The Kalapoya practiced sustainable harvesting methods for camas, ensuring that the plants could thrive for future generations. They used traditional techniques, such as baking the bulbs in underground ovens, to make them edible. This careful stewardship of the land and its resources reflects their deep understanding of the ecosystem.</li>\n<li><strong>Cultural Significance</strong></li>\n<li>Camas are considered a cultural keystone species, integral to the identity and traditions of the Kalapoya. The plant’s growth stages were often used as seasonal markers in their calendars, linking their agricultural practices to the rhythms of nature. The Kalapoya’s presence in the Beaverton area was driven by the availability of the camas and other resources, which were essential for their survival and cultural practice.</li>\n<li style=\"text-align: center;\">~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Follow the Mural on Instagram: #gatewaytothepast</strong></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-3817 aligncenter\" src=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Gateway-to-the-Past-Green-300x55.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Gateway-to-the-Past-Green-300x55.jpg 300w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Gateway-to-the-Past-Green-100x18.jpg 100w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Gateway-to-the-Past-Green-150x28.jpg 150w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Gateway-to-the-Past-Green-200x37.jpg 200w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Gateway-to-the-Past-Green-280x51.jpg 280w, https://raleighhillsbusinessassn.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Gateway-to-the-Past-Green.jpg 441w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"></p>\n<div>On behalf of the Raleigh Hills Business Association, we want to thank the mural committee for all of their efforts in seeing this project from idea to completion. It took so many people to make this happen and we would be very remiss in not thanking you for all that you have pulled off.</div>\n\n<div><u>Jason</u>&nbsp;- you had an idea, got the ball rolling, and this project would never have gotten off the ground without your tenacity and connections.</div>\n<div><u>Toni</u>&nbsp;- for being the biggest behind the scenes player and making RHBA look fantastic in the process. You made this happen with your efforts at securing funding, contacting local dignitaries, and making sure we had a big audience and eyes on this project. We could never have pulled this off&nbsp;without you. Your belief in the value and community benefit of the mural would be hard to exceed. And now we have a coloring book too, something to help keep this in the community's eyes for some time to come.</div>\n<div><u>Gabrielle</u>&nbsp;- you stepped in when the board needed some more eyes on the project. You made RHBA look good, competent, and above board, because of your efforts. We value your role and appreciate your offer to help out when it was needed.</div>\n<div><u>Diane</u>&nbsp;- You retired from the board and stepped in with both feet to the mural project. Your positive disposition, phoning skills, talking it up with your connections definitely made a big impact. Over 60 people were counted at the celebration and so many RHBA members were there...maybe more than any one time previously.</div>\n<div><u>Bev</u>&nbsp;- Never one to let a project linger, you stepped in to help out when it was needed. Your efforts have not gone unnoticed. We appreciate you for bringing so many people to the celebration, keeping the RHBA logo/brand/members out there front and center, and making sure we put a positive production together.</div>\n<div><u>Stacy Lynn Smith and Bob Hansen</u>&nbsp;- for your artwork and creativity that brought a dream to fruition.</div>\n\n<div>Like most of RHBA events, it takes a village...some in the forefront, and others working hard behind the scenes. Thank you all for your part. Courtyard Village put together a great spread, and the room looked as lovely as ever. The weather was perfect. It was a great day to celebrate both indoors and outdoors. Fred Meyer allowed this project to go forward, Explore Tualatin Valley, Venture Portland helped to fund the mural. The thanks go on and all. We appreciate all the partners in helping show that&nbsp;<i>RHBA is the Heart of the Community</i>!</div>\n</div></div></div></div></div>\t"
}